column2: The sky was partly cloudy and my kayak kept drifting as I was trying to do the disc reading.
The weather was sunny. I went out in a paddle boat which stayed in place better than the Kayak on the previous day.
The sky was sunny but clouds kept covering up the sun.
Partly cloudy- light winds out of the Southeast.
Mostly sunny skies.  Lake calm with light winds out of the East.  Moderate amounts of  pollen on lake surface.

After taking sechi disk reading- toured lake with John Preuss looking for invasive species. A check of the original site of eurasian milfoil found that site to be clean.  A new patch was found one dock to the east.  It is located about 30 ft off of the west corner of the dock.  Approximate GPS coordinates are: N 45 29' 42.0" and W 89 39' 43.8".  The patch size is about 3 ft by 4 ft.  It is now marked with a green bouy on its eastern edge.
Partly cloudy with a light West wind.  Lake water level is quite low.
Partly cloudy- calm lake- light breeze out of WSW
Partly cloudy with a light WNW wind.  Pair of loons kept me comany.
Mostly cloudy with a light SW wind.
Bright sunny day.  Secchi depth much lower than last time.
